# Copy to secrets.local (gitignored). Preferred format: NAME=VALUE, one per line.
# Blank lines + lines starting with # are ignored. A bare value (no NAME=) also
# works and gets an auto-generated name (SECRET_1, SECRET_2, ...).
#
# The NAME is used in the redaction marker sent upstream, e.g.
#   [REDACTED:DB_PASSWORD]
# so the model knows WHICH secret was censored and can reference it by name
# (env var / secrets file) without ever seeing the value. Names are metadata,
# not secrets - never put the secret in the name.
#
# The proxy redacts each VALUE and its encoded variants (base64 / base64url /
# url-encoded / json-escaped / hex) from every outgoing request body.
#
# Values shorter than 6 characters are rejected (too many false positives).
#
# Typical categories to cover:
#   DB_PASSWORD=...
#   DB_URL=...
#   PROXY_PASS=...
#   SSH_PASSWORD=...
#   SERVICE_API_KEY=...
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=...
#
# (Dynamic tokens - bearer tokens, cookies, auth tokens - are caught by the
#  REGEX layer, not this list; you don't need to enumerate those here.)
#
# EXAMPLE_KEY=example-do-not-use-me-123456
